body:
I don't find capture logs like in vscode
https://dartcode.org/docs/logging/  ?
(Specifically I was looking for how to get the logs in add2app scenario  and capture them to a file.  Probably this should be closed if the vscode feature is nothing like thhat

comment_data.body: @pq do we support anything like this in IntelliJ?

@pq I apologize, thehse aren't the droids I'm looking for :)
 I mean, these aren't the logs I'm looking for.

I was looking for flutter logs generated by print statements when running a flutter app. I actually do not know if that's what vscode saves; it may well be that the page I referenced is almost exactly like yours and not what i was looking for.

The problem I was trying to solve is that xcode and intellij were both frustratingly and inexplicably not showing any flutter logs in add2app scenario.

For some reason the problem went away after several days of being frustrated enough by it that i was attempting to build a log-via-file feature..

feel free to close this issue, especially if what i'm looking for is not a desired feature
thanks

> @pq I apologize, thehse aren't the droids I'm looking for :)

Haha!  (Aside: how can there not be a droid emoji on Github?!?!)

I'll close this out but cc @DanTup in case he has anything useful to add about what VSCode is doing.
